'''Bobby Henderson''' (born July 18, 1980) is the founder of [[Pastafarianism]]. He is a [[physics]] graduate from [[Oregon State University]]. He was born in [[Roseburg, Oregon]].

== Pastafarianism ==
In 2005, Henderson founded the religion of Pastafarianism in response to the [[Kansas evolution hearings|Kansas State Board of Education's decision]] to spend as much time teaching [[intelligent design]] as they did the [[Evolution (biology)|theory of evolution]].

Henderson claims that the Pastafarian theory of the origin of the world should be taught in the same way as intelligent design and the theory of evolution.

Pastafarianism asserts that the world was created in one day by the [[Flying Spaghetti Monster]], who created a mountain, then a tree, and finally a midget. The dogmas of Pastafarianism are centered on references to [[noodles]] and [[pirate]]s, and on parodies of [[creationist]] theories. Among other things, it is claimed that [[global warming]] is the result of the decline of the pirate population.

Henderson is the author of ''[[The Gospel of the Flying Spaghetti Monster]]''.<ref>Le Cherche midi, (March 12, 2008) {{ISBN|2749111188}}</ref>

