{{Other uses|Jean Robin (disambiguation){{!}}Jean Robin|Robin (disambiguation){{!}}Robin}}
'''Jean Robin''' (born in 1946) is a French writer and essayist, particularly interested in [[Occultism|occult]] and [[Esoterism|esoteric]] issues, [[Secret society|secret societies]] and their influence throughout history.
== Biography == [[File:Rennes-le-Château.jpg|thumb|left|<center>[[Rennes-le-Château]], one of the topics explored by Jean Robin</center>]]
It was at the beginning of his career at [[Éditions Robert Laffont]] that Jean Robin discovered [[René Guénon]]'s writings.<ref name= Camion>[https://books.google.com/books?id=MymUCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT17&dq=%22Jean+Robin+%22&hl=fr&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%20%22&f=false Entretien avec Jean Robin par le cercle II VIII XX XIV in "CAMION NOIR: HITLER L'élu du dragon"]</ref>
He subsequently produced the text (''René Guénon témoin de la Tradition'', 1978),<ref>[http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb346079631/PUBLIC FRBNF34607963]</ref><ref>[http://www.virgo-maria.org/D-Gnose-et-Contre-Eglise/Jean_Vaquie/Oeuvres/Vaquie-Imposture_guenonienne.pdf {{ill|Jean Vaquié|fr}}, {{isbn| 9781910220177}}]</ref><ref>[http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb34736211d Bnf catalogue]</ref> <ref>[http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb349058497 Bnf catalogue]</ref><ref>[http://www.persee.fr/doc/rhr_0035-1423_1981_num_198_2_4940?q=%22Jean%20Robin%22 [[Persée (web portal)|Persée]] " J. Robin. René Guénon, témoin de la Tradition" (compte-rendu), [[Jean-Pierre Laurant]] in ''Revue de l'histoire des religions'', year 1981, volume 198, No 2, (pp.&nbsp;233-234)]</ref> and has continued to make reference to the latter's work in other essays (''Le Royaume du Graal, ''1992;<ref>[http://www.sudoc.abes.fr/DB=2.1/SRCH?IKT=12&TRM=002877767 Sudoc abes]</ref> ''Veilleur, où en est la nuit'' (2000);<ref>[http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb370987571 Bnf catalogue]</ref> ''[[Howard Phillips Lovecraft|H.P. Lovecraft]] et le secret des adorateurs du Serpent'' 2017).<ref>[http://www.editions-tredaniel.com/lovecraft-et-le-secret-des-adorateurs-du-serpent-p-7129.html Editions-tredaniel]</ref><ref>[[Charles Upton (poet)|Charles Upton]] in [https://fa.livejournal.com/183495.html Live Journal]</ref>
The theme central to his work is [[eschatology]], which refers to the events that are thought to accompany the "end of our world" or historical-cosmological cycle. It is from the point of view of eschatology and with a Guenonian approach that he writes about themes such as "so-called aliens",<ref>[http://newsoftomorrow.org/ufologie/ombre/jean-robin-sur-les-ovnis-une-societe-secrete-mysterieuse-et-une-base-souterraine-pres-de-carcassonne Newsoftomorrow.org-ufologie, "Jean Robin sur les OVNIs, une société secrète mystérieuse et une base souterraine près de Carcassonne", 12 November 2012 | Published in Gouvernement de l'ombre]</ref><ref>{{en icon}}[https://books.google.fr/books?id=26v0qQcI0vwC&printsec=frontcover&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22%20Robin%22&f=false "Arktos: The Polar Myth in Science, Symbolism, and Nazi Survival", By [[Joscelyn Godwin]]]</ref><ref>{{en icon}}[https://books.google.com/books?id=M3q4DgAAQBAJ&pg=PA293&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22+ren%C3%A9+gu%C3%A9non+et+l%27initiation&hl=fr&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22%20ren%C3%A9%20gu%C3%A9non%20et%20l%27initiation&f=false Confessions of an Illuminati, VOLUME III: Espionage, Templars and Satanism ... Leo Lyon Zagami, Page 293]</ref> anti-initiation manipulation,<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=w8jkOf1rx7IC&pg=PA118&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22+ren%C3%A9+gu%C3%A9non+et+l%27initiation&hl=fr&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22%20ren%C3%A9%20gu%C3%A9non%20et%20l%27initiation&f=false in Politica Hermetica, L’age d’Homme Discussion générale, Jean-Pierre Laurant]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Tro9ZOeb92YC&pg=PA166&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22+ren%C3%A9+gu%C3%A9non+et+l%27initiation&hl=fr&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22%20contre%20initiation&f=false Julius Evola, métaphysicien et penseur politique: essai d'analyse structurale Par Jean-Paul Lippi, Page 166],</ref> <ref name= Camion/> [[Rennes-le-Château]],<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=01dGhFzE5FUC&pg=PA162&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjC7Mulx9DXAhWFmuAKHa9VBoo4ChDoAQg0MAM#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22&f=false "Mysteries of Templar Treasure & the Holy Grail: The Secrets of Rennes Le Chateau" By Lionel Fanthrope, Patricia Fanthrope, Page 162, Via Google books]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=nlIQUsY0LXoC&pg=PA105&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi617GrytDXAhWEm-AKHSusDJg4FBDoAQgwMAI#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22&f=false "The Canopus Revelation: The Stargate of the Gods and the Ark of Osiris" By Philip Coppens, page 105, Via Google books]</ref><ref>(fr)[http://www.portail-rennes-le-chateau.com/robin-salz.html Portail Rennes le château]</ref><ref>[http://www.persee.fr/docAsPDF/assr_0335-5985_1983_num_56_2_2301_t1_0300_0000_3.pdf Persée, Archives de sciences sociales des religions, "Robin (Jean), Rennes-le-Château, la colline envoûtée", [[Jean-Pierre Laurant]], Pdf],</ref> [[occultism in Nazism]],<ref>{{en icon}}[https://books.google.com/books?id=26v0qQcI0vwC&pg=PA127&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22+ren%C3%A9+gu%C3%A9non+et+l%27initiation&hl=fr&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22%20ren%C3%A9%20gu%C3%A9non%20et%20l%27initiation&f=false Arktos: The Polar Myth in Science, Symbolism, and Nazi Survival by Joscelyn Godwin]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=FQSLCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA116&dq=Jean+Robin+(writer)&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiS__iKitjXAhWk8oMKHbmGDt0Q6AEIPzAE#v=onepage&q=Jean%20Robin%20(writer)&f=false David Livingstone, ''Transhumanism: The History of a Dangerous Idea'']</ref> and the [[History of France]] and its mysteries.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=5zlqBgAAQBAJ&pg=PT540&dq=%22entretien+avec+Jean+Robin%22&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=snippet&q=%22Jean%20Robin%22&f=false in "Mystères et merveilles de l'histoire de France: L'Hexagone couronné", Bernard Fontaine, Geneviève Béduneau, J’ai lu, 2015 ]</ref><ref>Lionel Fanthrope, Patricia Fanthrope, ''Mysteries of Templar Treasure & the Holy Grail: The Secrets of Rennes Le Chateau'' page 161. [https://books.google.com/books?id=FTsEExrrQkIC&pg=PA161&dq=French+writer+Jean+Robin&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjNj-#v=onepage&q=French%20writer%20Jean%20Robin&f=false]</ref>
== Publications == === Works === * ''René Guénon, témoin de la tradition'', Paris, ed. [[Guy Trédaniel]], 1978, {{isbn|9782857070269}} (reissued. Robert Laffont, 1978), 355 p. * ''Les Objets volants non identifiés ou la Grande parodie'', Paris, Éditions de la Maisnie, 1979, 140 p., {{isbn|2-85707-038-1}}, translated into Spanish under the title ''UFO, la gran parodia''.<ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=X-U0ngAACAAJ&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22&hl=ensa=Xredir_esc=y%20editeur:%20All%27insegna%20del%20Veltro,%201984en%20espagnol%20 ''UFO, la gran parodia'']</ref> * ''Réponse de Nostradamus à Monsieur de Fontbrune'', Paris, Éditions de la Maisnie, 1981, 133 p., {{isbn|2-85707-075-6}}, translated into Spanish under the title ''Respuesto de Nostradamus a Monsieur de Fontbrune'', Esoteria (1982), {{isbn| 9788485411696}}.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/respuestade-nostradamus-a-monsieur-de-fontbrune/oclc/50544762&referer=brief_results WorldCatalog]</ref> * ''Rennes-le-Château. La colline envoûtée'', Paris, Éditions de la Maisnie, 1982, {{isbn|2-85-707082-9}} * ''René Guénon. La dernière chance de l'Occident'', Paris, Éditions de la Maisnie, 1983, 206 p, {{isbn|9782857071020}} * ''Les Sociétés secrètes au rendez-vous de l'Apocalypse'', Paris, Guy Trédaniel and Éd. de la Maisnie, 1985, 390 p., {{isbn|978-7629435604}} translated into Spanish under the title ''Las sociedades secretas en la cita del Apocalipsis'' {{isbn|9788478920143}}.<ref>[https://books.google.fr/books?id=WmO7AQAACAAJ&dq=%22Jean+Robin%22&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y%20Heptada%20Ediciones,%201990 ''Las sociedades secretas en la cita del Apocalipsis'']</ref> * ''Thèbes, Temples et Dieux du Nil'', [[Éditions Robert Laffont]], 1986, 138 p., {{isbn|978-2221504291}} * ''La véritable mission du Comte de Saint-Germain'', Guy Trédaniel, 1986, 125 p., {{isbn|978-2857072010}} * ''Seth, le dieu maudit'', éditions Guy Trédaniel, 1986, 249 p., {{isbn|978-2857071976}} * ''Hitler, l'élu du dragon'', Paris, Éditions de la Maisnie, 1987, 239 p., {{isbn|9782857072447}}.<ref>[https://www.scribd.com/document/17429348/Jean-Robin-Hitler-l-Elu-Du-Dragon Scrid document]</ref> translated into Spanish under the title ''Hitler, el elegido del dragón'', Colección Enigmas de la historia, Roca, 1991, {{isbn |9788427015647}},<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=FK4tAAAACAAJ&dq=%22Jean+Robin+%22&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwionuzchJPUAhUDuBoKHUSoCGA4FBDoAQgmMAA Hitler, el elegido del dragón]</ref><ref>{{es}}[https://mparalelos.jimdo.com/2013/04/03/los-ovnis-de-los-nazis/ "Los ovnis de los nazis"]</ref><ref>{{es}}[http://ignacioondargain.tripod.com/id47.html LOS GUARDIANES DE LA SANGRE ETERNA]</ref> reissue November 2015 with a preface and an interview with the author, 314 p, Camion Noir publisher, {{isbn| 978-2357797307}}. * ''Opération Orth ou l'Incroyable secret de Rennes-le-Château'', Paris, Guy Trédaniel, 1989, 269 p., {{isbn|978-2857073086}} * {{Cite book|title= Le Royaume du Graal, Introduction au mystère de la France|publisher=Éditions Trédaniel|year=1992 |pages =764| isbn=978-2-85707-539-4| url=http://www.editions-tredaniel.com/le-royaume-du-graal-p-364.html}} * {{Cite book|title= Veilleur, où en est la nuit ? Introduction à l'Apocalypse|publisher=Éditions Trédaniel |year=2000 |pages= 344|isbn=978-2-84445-155-2 |url=http://www.editions-tredaniel.com/veilleur-ou-en-est-la-nuit-p-2397.html}} * {{Cite book|title= Imperator, l'épopée de Julien l'Apostat, Roman historique|publisher=Éditions Trédaniel|year= 2013|pages= 260|isbn=978-2-8132-0574-2|url=http://www.editions-tredaniel.com/imperator-p-5471.html}} * {{Cite book|title= H.P. Lovecraft et le secret des adorateurs du serpent |location= Paris|publisher=Éditions Trédaniel |year= 2017|page= 456|isbn= 978-2-8132-0990-0 | url=http://www.editions-tredaniel.com/lovecraft-et-le-secret-des-adorateurs-du-serpent-p-7129.html}}.
=== Magazines === Jean Robin has contributed to several magazines: * ''{{ill|Nouvelle École|fr}}'' n° 41, Littérature et idéologie 2, Autumn 1984, ''René Guénon ou la Tradition retrouvée'', (pp.&nbsp;92–95)<ref>[http://grece-fr.com/?p=1457 Groupement de recherche et d’études pour la civilisation européenne - Nouvelle École n°41: Littérature et idéologie 2]</ref> The article is followed by a bibliography signed N. E. , of René Guénon's work and biographical studies. In it is also published an article by René Guénon published in Italian (translated by Evola or perhaps having rewritten (or synthesized) a passage from the ''Chaos social'' chapt. 6 of ''La Crise moderne''). Translation {{ill|Philippe Baillet (traducteur)|fr|Philippe Baillet (traducteur)|lt=Philippe Baillet}}. * Collective work ''[[L'Herne|Les Cahiers de l'Herne]]'', N°49 (1985), devoted to René Guénon: author of the article entitled ''Le problème du mal dans l'œuvre de René Guénon'', (pp.&nbsp;102–112).<ref>[https://www.scribd.com/document/32058508/Cahier-N-49-Rene-Guenon Scrid, Cahier-N-49-Rene-Guenon]</ref> * Revue L'age d'or, winter 1987, interview with Jean Robin about his book "Seth le dieu maudit".
